#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:928
#, no-c-format
msgid "It is important to remember that you define your own \"language\" when using simon. That means that you are not bound to grammar rules that exist in whatever language you want to use simon with. For a simple command and control use-case it would for example be advisable to invent new grammatical rules to eliminate the differences between different commands imposed by grammatical information not relevant for this use case."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:932
#, no-c-format
msgid "In the example above it is for example not relevant that \"close\" is a verb or that \"Computer\" and \"Internet\" are nouns. Instead, why not define them as something that better reflects what we want them to be:"
